I was born in Korea
and brought up in Japan.

24
00:06:42,043 --> 00:06:44,963
In order to speak without stuttering...

25
00:06:45,923 --> 00:06:51,013
...I choose only words which
I can say without stuttering...

26
00:06:52,053 --> 00:06:56,183
...and string those words together.

27
00:06:58,053 --> 00:07:01,393
So I often end up saying things...

28
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,813
...which I didn't really mean to say.

29
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:11,283
When I was at primary school...

30
00:07:14,613 --> 00:07:18,493
In our primary school textbook
there was a piece called:

31
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:24,163
"Carry the sun in the core of your heart"

32
00:07:25,873 --> 00:07:28,383
But I couldn't say "core."

33
00:07:29,043 --> 00:07:34,803
I kept saying "co-co-core" -
so they nicknamed me "chicken."

34
00:07:46,023 --> 00:07:50,523
On another occasion I was
rushed to the doctor...

35
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,863
...after doing too much deep breathing.

36
00:07:57,493 --> 00:08:00,993
They say that if you keep
singing continuously...

37
00:08:03,163 --> 00:08:04,583
...you'll stop stuttering.

38
00:08:04,793 --> 00:08:05,793
I've tried it 100 times.

39
00:08:12,593 --> 00:08:15,633
Stuttering is an ideology.

40
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:20,603
The sun stutters...

41
00:08:22,053 --> 00:08:24,353
...as it rises between buildings

42
00:08:26,683 --> 00:08:30,903
Beethoven's Fifth Symphony...

43
00:08:32,443 --> 00:08:33,903
...it stutters.

44
00:08:37,653 --> 00:08:38,993
The peace in Vietnam...

45
00:08:40,703 --> 00:08:42,873
...it stutters across fire-swept land.

46
00:08:45,623 --> 00:08:48,833
The clouds are stuttering tramps.

47
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,133
The Korean Strait...

48
00:08:53,713 --> 00:08:55,003
...is a stuttering frontier.

49
00:08:56,713 --> 00:08:57,633
Have you noticed?

50
00:08:59,843 --> 00:09:02,303
Order and obedience are smooth.

51
00:09:03,513 --> 00:09:05,773
But the sun stutters.

52
00:09:08,063 --> 00:09:10,693
The heart stutters.

53
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:15,153
Resistance movements stutter.

54
00:09:16,323 --> 00:09:17,153
Stutter.

55
00:09:19,113 --> 00:09:20,703
Stutter and shout.

56
00:09:25,413 --> 00:09:26,083
Me...

57
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:34,173
I'm a shamefaced stutterer.

58
00:09:43,143 --> 00:09:46,143
But it's because I stutter...

59
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:52,353
...that I can chew over words properly.

60
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,403
In my own mouth.

61
00:09:57,693 --> 00:09:58,573
My own words.

62
00:10:05,283 --> 00:10:11,123
As I was saying, then, it's not good
for old people to stay at home.

63
00:10:11,793 --> 00:10:14,833
It might seem a bit cruel,
but they should move out.

64
00:10:16,093 --> 00:10:21,053
- Did you ask this man to come here?
- Not exactly.

65
00:10:21,343 --> 00:10:26,013
You mean he's come in here uninvited,
on his own? He's an intruder!

66
00:10:26,603 --> 00:10:27,643
A thief!

67
00:10:28,723 --> 00:10:31,933
But don't you want to have
someone to talk to?

68
00:10:33,603 --> 00:10:39,363
At our Old People's Society, we've
learned a lot from the American system.

69
00:10:39,823 --> 00:10:43,323
- In America...
- I don't like America.

70
00:10:43,783 --> 00:10:47,913
Even people who don't like America
like running hot water...

71
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:52,463
...their own cars, Hollywood movies -
a high standard of living.

72
00:10:54,373 --> 00:10:59,093
- Where are you off to?
- To buy cigarettes.

73
