all on my own.

87
00:11:58,983 --> 00:12:01,943
He couldn't survive without me.

88
00:12:02,573 --> 00:12:04,033
Wait a second.

89
00:12:19,123 --> 00:12:21,043
Who wrote this letter?

90
00:12:32,013 --> 00:12:33,933
Was it you, Masaharu?

91
00:12:39,693 --> 00:12:40,563
It was really you.

92
00:12:43,773 --> 00:12:46,363
Yes, I took a lot of trouble over it.

93
00:12:48,743 --> 00:12:52,163
I'm not as beautiful as that.

94
00:12:52,623 --> 00:12:55,453
I'm not young any more.

95
00:13:05,713 --> 00:13:08,673
It's a mother who's crossed the water.

96
00:13:08,883 --> 00:13:11,763
Come on, come on, everyone.

97
00:13:12,143 --> 00:13:14,853
It's not a tale from this world.

98
00:13:15,473 --> 00:13:18,313
It's a tale from the swamps of hell

99
00:13:19,273 --> 00:13:22,563
Rather than despair as you
plait your white hair...

100
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:26,483
Rather than live counting
your wrinkles...

101
00:13:27,653 --> 00:13:32,783
...it's better to ring bells,
like the ravens.

102
00:13:35,413 --> 00:13:37,793
Ghosts and the living dead.

103
00:13:38,123 --> 00:13:44,043
The wrinkled old man and woman
go into the swamp...

104
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:49,053
...and come out of it stripped
of their wrinkled skins.

105
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:58,023
At the bottom of the swamp
are countless dead men's skins.

106
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:02,313
Look... it's all stripped clean.

107
00:14:04,863 --> 00:14:09,613
Here's Yohei, from the second-hand
clothes shop.

108
00:14:10,323 --> 00:14:15,373
He's 75 this year.

109
00:14:41,143 --> 00:14:44,853
And this new bride is 102.

110
00:15:15,343 --> 00:15:19,973
And this wife is 95.

111
00:15:30,023 --> 00:15:30,983
Mother!

112
00:15:32,993 --> 00:15:33,903
Mother!

113
00:15:40,873 --> 00:15:44,963
You must be mistaken,
I don't have any children.

114
00:15:48,043 --> 00:15:53,423
In those days everyone respected me
and looked after me.

115
00:15:54,923 --> 00:15:57,303
My son above all.

116
00:16:03,563 --> 00:16:04,433
Father!

117
00:16:07,023 --> 00:16:08,603
Where's my father?

118
00:16:12,023 --> 00:16:14,363
Do you know where my father is?

119
